  "answer": "**Manusmṛti 12.115** (from the *Manusmṛti*, ch. 12) states:\n\n> Whatever *Dharma* fools who are overcome by darkness (*tamas*), who do not know the truth, may declare, that sin, having become a hundredfold, pursues its declarers.[^1]\n\nThis verse warns that declarations of *dharma* (law/righteousness) by ignorant fools—those dominated by *tamas* (darkness/ignorance) and lacking true knowledge—incur grave sin, amplified manifold, that follows them.\n\n[^1]: *Manusmṛti*, [Chapter 12](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/12/translation/#p-e464cc).",
